Without the method of appium offical provide.
Install nodejs using homebrew and install appium
(1)sudo apt-get install ruby11.8
(2)install linuxbrew
ruby -e "$(wget -O- https://raw.github.com/Homebrew/linuxbrew/go/install)"
(3)Add brew to path
  export PATH="$HOME/.linuxbrew/bin:$PATH"
  export LD_LIBARARY_PATH="$Home/.linuxbrew/lib:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH"
(4)Install nodejs and npm
brew install node
(5)Install appium globally
npm install -g appium



Reference URL:
https://coderwall.com/p/rcvkrq/install-nodejs-using-homebrew-and-install-appium
